<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She never puts a foot wrong in the fashion stakes.</p>

<p>And on Sunday, Phoebe Burgess showed off her penchant for fashion in a number of candid shots shared to Instagram Stories.</p>

<p>The 31-year-old ex-wife of NRL star Sam Burgess, broke down her $6,524 designer outfit, which included the coveted $3,850 yellow Bottega Veneta Cassette bag. </p>

<p>Dripping in style! Phoebe Burgess (pictured), 31, worked her angles in a $6K designer outfit this week, including the coveted Bottega Veneta handbag favoured by the A-list </p>

<p>Posing on a quiet street, Phoebe looked in her element as she showed off her tailored garb.</p>

<p>The influencer donned a white Camilla and Marc dress shirt, retailing for $320, which she said 'every wardrobe needs stat'. </p>

<p>Phoebe teamed the top with a tailored black pant by Bassike, retailing for approximately $550, and kept light on her feet with white suede platform slip-ons by The Row, retailing for USD $790 (AUD $1124).</p>

